fields.description:
The page at http://localhost:6060/foo/plugins/servlet/oauth/consumers/list looks bad.

It has it's own stylesheet (see below) but that must make assumptions about its environment which are incorrect.

{noformat}
#oauth-plugin {}
      #oauth-plugin p {
          margin: 0 0 0.5em 0;
          max-width: 36em;
      }
      #oauth-plugin a.anchor,
      #oauth-plugin a.anchor:hover {
          color: #333;
          cursor: default;
          text-decoration: none;
       }

  #oauth-plugin div.content {
      margin: 0 20em 2em 0;
  }
      #oauth-plugin div.content p.description {
          margin: 0 0 2em 0;
      }

  #oauth-plugin div.subcontent {
      background: #e0efff;
      border: 1px solid #9eb6d4;
      float: right;
      margin: 0 1em 1em 1.5em;
      padding: 1em 1em 0.5em 1em;
      width: 20em;
  }

  form#add-by-url {
      margin: 0 0 2em 0;
  }
  
  form#oauth-authorize {
      padding: 1em 0 1em 0;
  }

  #oauth-plugin table {
      background-color: #fcfcfc;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      border: 1px solid #d2d2d2;
  }

      #oauth-plugin table th,
      #oauth-plugin table td {
          border: 1px solid #d2d2d2;
          padding: 4px;
          vertical-align: top;
      }

      #oauth-plugin table th {
          background-color: #e2e2e2;
          text-align: left;
      }
      
  #oauth-plugin form {
      max-width: 36em;
  }
      #oauth-plugin form h2 {
          clear: none;
      }
{noformat}

A disabled repository should not affect api calls to list repositories. 

The disabled git repository is a customer's environment was throwing errors such as 

{noformat}
Repository REPONMAE on http://HOST:8060/ failed: repository not in correct state: Repository is stopped 
{noformat}

in JIRA when viewing "All" activity in JIRA or when viewing a JIRA project which is not associated with a Fisheye repository (and hence searches all repositories).

